public Snapshot(Long snapshotID,
                   Long volumeID,
                   String volumePairUUID,
                   String name,
                   String checksum,
                   String status,
                   Long totalSize,
                   Optional<Long> groupID,
                   String createTime,
                   Map<String,Object> attributes)
        Snapshots is an object containing information about each snapshot made for a volume. The return object includes information for the active snapshot as well as each snapshot created for the volume.
        Parameters:
        snapshotID - [required] Unique ID for this snapshot.
        volumeID - [required] The volume this snapshot was taken of.
        volumePairUUID - [required] Universal identifier of the volume pair
        name - [required] A name for this snapshot.
        checksum - [required] A string that represents the correct digits in the stored snapshot.
        status - [required] Current status of the snapshot
        totalSize - [required] Total size of this snapshot in bytes.
        groupID - (optional) If present, the ID of the group this snapshot is a part of.
        createTime - [required] The time this snapshot was taken.
        attributes - [required] List of Name/Value pairs in JSON object format.
        Since:
        7.0

      • Snapshot

        @Since(value="8.0")
public Snapshot(Long snapshotID,
                   Long volumeID,
                   String volumePairUUID,
                   String name,
                   String checksum,
                   Boolean enableRemoteReplication,
                   String expirationReason,
                   String expirationTime,
                   String remoteStatuses,
                   String status,
                   String uUID,
                   Long totalSize,
                   Optional<Long> groupID,
                   String groupSnapshotUUID,
                   String createTime,
                   Map<String,Object> attributes)
        Snapshots is an object containing information about each snapshot made for a volume. The return object includes information for the active snapshot as well as each snapshot created for the volume.
        Parameters:
        snapshotID - [required] Unique ID for this snapshot.
        volumeID - [required] The volume this snapshot was taken of.
        volumePairUUID - [required] Universal identifier of the volume pair
        name - [required] A name for this snapshot.
        checksum - [required] A string that represents the correct digits in the stored snapshot.
        enableRemoteReplication - [required] Identifies if snapshot is enabled for remote replication.
        expirationReason - [required] Indicates how the snapshot expiration was set. Possible values
        expirationTime - [required] The time at which this snapshot will expire and be purged from the cluster.
        remoteStatuses - [required] Current remote status of the snapshot
        status - [required] Current status of the snapshot
        uUID - [required] Universal Unique ID of an existing snapshot.
        totalSize - [required] Total size of this snapshot in bytes.
        groupID - (optional) If present, the ID of the group this snapshot is a part of.
        groupSnapshotUUID - [required] The current “members” results contains information about each snapshot in the group.
        createTime - [required] The time this snapshot was taken.
        attributes - [required] List of Name/Value pairs in JSON object format.
        Since:
        8.0

        A string that represents the correct digits in the stored snapshot. This checksum can be used later to compare other snapshots to detect errors in the data.

        @Since(value="8.0")
public String getExpirationReason()
        Indicates how the snapshot expiration was set. Possible values api: expiration time was set by using the API. none: there is no expiration time set. test: expiration time was set for testing.
        Since:
        8.0

      • getRemoteStatuses

        @Since(value="8.0")
public String getRemoteStatuses()
        Current remote status of the snapshot remoteStatus: Possible values Present: Snapshot exists on a remote cluster
        Not Present: Snapshot does not exist on remote cluster
        Syncing: This is a target cluster and it is currently replicating the snapshot
        Deleted: This is a target cluster, the snapshot has been deleted, and it still exists on the source.
        volumePairUUID: universal identifier of the volume pair
        Since:
        8.0

      • getStatus

        public String getStatus()
        Current status of the snapshot
        Preparing: A snapshot that is being prepared for use and is not yet writable.
        Done: A snapshot that has finished being prepared and is now usable.
        Active: This snapshot is the active branch.

      • getTotalSize

        public Long getTotalSize()
        Total size of this snapshot in bytes. It is equivalent to totalSize of the volume when this snapshot was taken.

      • getGroupID

        public Optional<Long> getGroupID()
        If present, the ID of the group this snapshot is a part of. If not present, this snapshot is not part of a group.

      • getGroupSnapshotUUID
